<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-9198] StopReplica handler should complete pending purgatory operations</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-9198</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a reassignment completes, the current leader may need to be shutdown with a StopReplica request. It may still have fetch/produce requests in purgatory when this happens. We do not have logic currently to force completion of these requests which means they are doomed to eventually timeout. This is mostly an issue for produce requests which use the default request timeout of 30s.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13268870">KAFKA-9198</key>
            <summary>StopReplica handler should complete pending purgatory operations</summary>
