                            <comment id="16975770" author="githubbot" created="Sat, 16 Nov 2019 18:10:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;hachikuji commented on pull request #7701: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-9198&quot; title=&quot;StopReplica handler should complete pending purgatory operations&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-9198&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-9198&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; Complete purgatory operations on receiving StopReplica&lt;br/&gt;
URL: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/7701&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/7701&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;   Force completion of delayed operations when receiving a StopReplica request. In the case of a partition reassignment, we cannot rely on receiving a LeaderAndIsr request in order to complete these operations because the leader may no longer be a replica. Previously when this happened, the delayed operations were left to eventually timeout. &lt;/p&gt;

